# Component Rules

## Naming

- PascalCase filenames: `HeaderAesthetics.tsx`, `SectionBeforeAfter.tsx`
- Admin components prefixed with `Admin`: `AdminGalleryManager.tsx`
- Section components prefixed with `Section`: `SectionNewsletter.tsx`

## Client Components

Most components use `"use client"` because they need interactivity. Mark at the top of the file.

## HeroUI Usage

- Import from `@heroui/react` for common components (Modal, Button, Card, etc.)
- Import from individual packages for specific ones: `@heroui/chip`, `@heroui/input`, `@heroui/select`, `@heroui/spinner`
- Never import from `@nextui/*` — always use `@heroui/*`

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS classes
- Custom colors from `config/colors.ts` (e.g., `aestheticsColors.green.DEFAULT`)
- Dark mode support with `dark:` prefix
- Design tokens from `config/design-system.ts` and **`config/typography.ts`** for headings and layout (see `.cursor/rules/typography-responsive.mdc`)
- The main green color is `#464C45`
- **Responsive typography:** Use `typography.headingPage`, `typography.headingSection`, `typography.headingCard` etc. so titles scale on mobile (no raw `text-4xl`/`text-5xl` without smaller mobile size)
- **Containers:** Use `layout.container` (`max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`) for section content; `layout.containerNarrow` for forms

## Hydration Safety

- Always render the same DOM structure on server and client
- Do NOT conditionally render different root elements based on client-only state
- Use `hidden` class to hide/show elements instead of conditional rendering that changes tree shape
- Use `suppressHydrationWarning` on elements with dynamic content
- Wrap client-only components in `<ClientOnly>` from `@/components/ClientOnly`

## Phone / Contact Data in Components

- Components that display or link to a phone number (e.g. `ButtonCallNow`, `ButtonWhatsApp`, `SectionContact`, `FooterMain`) must resolve phone via: `useAdminProfile().profile.phone` → `siteConfig.contact.phone`.
- Never hardcode a specific phone number as a fallback (e.g. `"0800 123 4567"` or `"+44 7541777225"`). Always fall back to `siteConfig.contact.phone`.
- For WhatsApp: use `adminProfile.whatsapp` → `adminProfile.phone` → `siteConfig.contact.whatsapp`.

## Empty Data Sections

- When a component section renders data from the DB (e.g. transport options, landmarks, service areas): **hide the section** when data is empty or only contains default placeholder text.
- Do not show generic placeholder text like "We are conveniently located near major transport links" when no real data has been entered.

## Image Handling

- Use `lib/image-utils.ts` for processing, compression, and format support
- Support HEIC conversion via `heic2any`
- Provide quality sliders for image compression in upload forms
